Colombian Stock Movers: Empresa de Energia de Bogota, Enka

-- B y   B l a k e   S c h m i d t
-- 
2011-10-07T20:45:06Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-07/colombian-stock-movers-empresa-de-energia-de-bogota-enka.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4 p.m.  New York  time.  The IGBC Index fell 0.7 percent to 12,871.86 while the
Colcap Index declined 0.4 percent to 1,583.86.  Empresa de Energia de Bogota SA (EEB)  , Colombia’s
second-biggest electricity distributor, rose 3.8 percent, the
most in a week, to 1,365 pesos. The company’s shareholders
approved today the sale of $610 million in 10-year bonds to be
sold in New York.  EEB, as the state-controlled company is known, will use the
funds to buy back as much as $610 million of its EEB
International Ltd. bond due 2014, Monica De Greiff, the
company’s president, told reporters in Bogota. The bond
repurchase will begin as soon as Oct. 31, she said.  Enka de Colombia SA (ENKA)  , a Medellin-based synthetic
fibers producer, rose 1.9 percent to 10.8 pesos. Senate Majority
Leader  Harry Reid  said yesterday he wants lawmakers to vote on
pending free-trade agreements with South Korea, Colombia and
Panama on Oct. 12.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Blake Schmidt in Bogota at 
 bschmidt16@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
